From b0000000000000000000000000000000000000023 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: gregordinary <33880035+gregordinary@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sat, 19 Jul 2026 12:00:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] clk: rockchip: rk3576: keep the CNTPCT source on the 24 MHz
 oscillator

The high-precision timer at 0x27400000 drives the ARM generic counter
(CNTPCT), and rockchip_stimer_init() advertises it to the kernel as
24 MHz via CNTFRQ_EL0. Its clock, CLK_HPTIMER_SRC, muxes between CPLL
and the 24 MHz oscillator (PMU_CLKSEL_CON(11) bit 6) and selects CPLL
out of reset. That is only 24 MHz while CPLL is in slow mode; once the
SoC bring-up puts CPLL in normal mode the counter runs at the full CPLL
rate while CNTFRQ still reads 24 MHz. The kernel then scales every
timestamp by the PLL multiple - a fast boot logs as tens of minutes -
and every time-derived hardware operation (USB reset and timeout
windows, I2C transfer timeouts, udelay) is off by the same factor and
fails.

Point CLK_HPTIMER_SRC at the 24 MHz oscillator, divided by one, so
CNTPCT stays 24 MHz regardless of CPLL's mode.

Signed-off-by: gregordinary <33880035+gregordinary@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 drivers/clk/rockchip/clk_rk3576.c | 8 ++++++++
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/clk/rockchip/clk_rk3576.c b/drivers/clk/rockchip/clk_rk3576.c
index 42fc30bd..43fc30be 100644
--- a/drivers/clk/rockchip/clk_rk3576.c
+++ b/drivers/clk/rockchip/clk_rk3576.c
@@ -2586,6 +2586,14 @@ static void rk3576_clk_init_spl(void)
 	       RK3576_CRU_BASE + RK3576_MODE_CON0);
 	writel(BITS_WITH_WMASK(1, 0x3U, 8),
 	       RK3576_CRU_BASE + RK3576_MODE_CON0);
+	/*
+	 * The high-precision timer feeding the ARM generic counter (CNTPCT)
+	 * selects CPLL by default; with CPLL now in normal mode it would
+	 * clock the counter far above the 24 MHz that CNTFRQ advertises and
+	 * inflate every kernel timestamp. Pin it to the 24 MHz oscillator.
+	 */
+	writel(BITS_WITH_WMASK(1, 0x1U, 6) | BITS_WITH_WMASK(0, 0x1fU, 1),
+	       RK3576_CRU_BASE + RK3576_PMU_CLKSEL_CON(11));
 	/* init cci */
 	writel(0xffff0000, RK3576_CRU_BASE + RK3576_CCI_CLKSEL_CON(4));
 	rockchip_pll_set_rate(&rk3576_pll_clks[BPLL], cru, BPLL, LPLL_HZ);
